Disabled regression test for issue #1081: a `cast` whose operand contains an undefined symbol can drive the IL emitter into a "generated dummy value" internal compiler error rather than reporting the underlying symbol-not-found at semantic time.

Currently:

```
test.ghul: 12,41..12,78: fatal: generated dummy value: !!! from test.ghul 12,41..12,77
internal compiler error
```

Expected behaviour: the diagnostic should be the original `symbol not found: undefined_handler` (or similar) and the build should fail cleanly without an internal-error/dummy-value path.

Re-enable by deleting this `disabled` file once the error-value propagation is tightened so the cast doesn't synthesise a dummy.
